 :tx/rationale "Create task: DAEMON-1: Incremental Store — Store::apply_tx(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) for O(k) in-place mutation (INV-STORE-001, ADR-STORE-005). BACKGROUND: Currently Store is immutable — from_datoms() rebuilds all 5 indexes from scratch in O(n). The daemon needs to apply transactions incrementally without full rebuild. APPROACH: (1) Add pub fn apply_tx(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) to Store. For each datom: insert into self.datoms (BTreeSet), push to entity_index[d.entity], push to attribute_index[d.attribute], if Value::Ref push to vaet_index[target], if Op::Assert push to avet_index[(attr,val)], update live_view[(entity,attr)] with LWW resolution. (2) Update frontier with tx's agent→clock. (3) Update schema if any :db/* attributes change. (4) Property: apply_tx(datoms) must produce identical Store state as from_datoms(old_datoms ∪ new_datoms). This is the isomorphism invariant. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Property test: for any store S and transaction T, S.apply_tx(T) == Store::from_datoms(S.datom_set() ∪ T). (B) apply_tx is O(k) where k = |T|, verified by timing at 1K/10K/100K store sizes. (C) All 5 indexes consistent after apply_tx (entity, attribute, vaet, avet, live). (D) Schema updated when :db/* attributes in transaction. (E) Frontier monotonically advances. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs"
